# Frontend Patterns

## Next.js App Router

### Server vs Client components
- Default to **Server Components** — add `'use client'` only when needed
- `'use client'` is required for: hooks, event handlers, browser APIs, TanStack Query
- Never use `useEffect` to fetch data — use TanStack Query or Server Component data fetching

### File conventions
- Pages: `app/<route>/page.tsx` — always export `metadata` for SEO
- Layouts: `app/<route>/layout.tsx`
- Components: `components/<domain>/<component-name>.tsx`
- Hooks: `hooks/use-<name>.ts`
- API helpers: `lib/<domain>.ts`

## TanStack Query

### Always use query key factory
```ts
// lib/query-keys.ts
export const queryKeys = {
  scenarios: {
    history: () => ['scenarios', 'history'] as const,
  },
};
```

### Data fetching pattern
```ts
const { data, isLoading } = useQuery({
  queryKey: queryKeys.scenarios.history(),
  queryFn: scenariosApi.history,
  select: (res) => res.data,   // unwrap envelope
});
```

### Mutation + cache invalidation
```ts
const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: scenariosApi.run,
  onSuccess: () => {
    void queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: queryKeys.scenarios.history() });
  },
});
```

### Never use raw fetch in components
- All API calls go through `lib/api.ts` → domain API module → TanStack Query

## React Hook Form

### Always pair with Zod
```ts
const schema = z.object({ type: z.enum(SCENARIO_TYPES) });
type FormValues = z.infer<typeof schema>;
const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm<FormValues>({ resolver: zodResolver(schema) });
```

### shadcn Select with RHF
- Use `setValue` from `useForm` in the `onValueChange` callback — not `register`

## shadcn/ui

### Component usage
- Always import from `@/components/ui/<component>` — never from `@radix-ui` directly in pages
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging — never string concatenation
- Badge variants: `success` | `warning` | `destructive` | `info` | `default`

### Layout primitives
- `PageShell` — outermost wrapper for every page
- `SectionHeader` — title + description + optional action slot
- `Card` / `CardHeader` / `CardContent` — for all content panels

## Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes — no inline styles
- Use CSS variables from `globals.css` for brand colours: `text-primary`, `text-signal-success`, etc.
- Animations: use `animate-slide-up`, `animate-pulse-ring` from tailwind config
